1
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,240
There was a tape hidden in this.

2
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,520
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,760
And I never knew! Damn it!

4
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,680
What does Puna have to do with this?

5
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,640
Because Puna

6
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:43,840
is Phupha's daughter.

7
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:48,720
<i>Don't let anyone grab these hands</i>

8
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:51,480
I already sold this song
to Darathong Music.

9
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,520
Chaiya and Manat

10
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:57,080
were hanging around
near the phone repair shop.

11
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,080
POL.CAPT. CHAIYA DEVAPITHAK
POL.LT. MANAT ASWASUKPHONG

12
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:00,680
Chaiya and Manat are cops!

13
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:04,600
I'm really pissed!
I never thought those two were cops!

14
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,280
But I need to be honest.

15
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,040
There's no way this can work

16
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,360
between us.

17
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:13,720
You guys deserve to die like stray dogs.

18
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,240
Chaiya!

19
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,240
This is for you!

20
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,040
Let's go.

21
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,640
Get out of here now! Hurry!

22
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,839
Where are they?!

23
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:24,000
Lucky for them I didn't get there in time,

24
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,720
or they'd all be dead.

25
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,040
Really, Sergeant?

26
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:29,560
-Huh? Why?
-Another 50 are coming.

27
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,760
Another 50 coming? No problem!

28
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,160
I'll hide behind you.

29
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,320
Alright.

30
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,720
Lieutenant, stay with me.

31
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,680
I've been ordered to arrest you.

32
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,280
What did you just say?

33
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:48,000
You heard right.
It's the superintendent's order.

34
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:50,600
Right now, the three of you are in danger.

35
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,800
They're setting it up

36
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:54,040
to make all three of you the criminals.

37
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,280
What's going on?

38
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,720
Why are the cops suddenly the bad guys?

39
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,640
Their connections and power

40
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,640
can make anything happen.

41
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,720
Come on. I'll take you to the safe house.

42
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,760
Lead the way, Captain. I'll follow.

43
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,000
Corporal Chom, follow me.

44
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:29,680
After this, I probably
won't see you again.

45
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,920
Or you'd be in danger.

46
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,720
What about you?

47
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:37,800
Don't worry about me. I'll be fine.

48
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:43,040
Here, I'm keeping it to protect me.

49
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:54,080
You're a good person.
Your goodness will keep you safe.

50
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,760
Puna.

51
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,320
Take care of yourself too.

52
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,440
You too.

53
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,320
Promise me you'll come back safe.

54
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,080
I promise.

55
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,400
Chaiya!

56
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,400
We need to go now! Hurry!

57
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:30,400
I have to go.

58
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,440
Take good care of yourself.

59
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:10,920
DARATHONG MUSIC

60
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,520
How come you two are together?

61
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:22,200
Sonrak ended up
stuck in the middle of a hail of bullets.

62
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,160
Luckily, he didn't get hit.

63
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:28,920
Dad, what happened? Why were Chit
and Chaiya shooting at each other?

64
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,680
Well…

65
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:35,440
Chaiya and Manat are drug dealers.

66
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:38,040
When I caught them,
they tried to take us out.

67
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,240
Last time,

68
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:42,800
our car got searched by the police

69
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,320
-at the concert, remember?
-Yes.

70
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,600
That was their doing.

71
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:50,000
They used our car to move drugs?

72
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,240
Yeah.

73
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:53,160
And it wasn't just once.

74
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,880
Think back.

75
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,680
When we were doing the donation event
with Kamnan Pong,

76
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:01,520
our donation truck got searched too.

77
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:05,800
Since they started working at our company,

78
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,520
Chaiya and Manat

79
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:12,680
have done a lot to damage the reputation
of our Darathong Music label.

80
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:19,280
Dad, I'm sorry. I didn't realize
I was bringing criminals into the company.

81
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,000
Don't blame yourself.

82
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:26,080
It's not your fault, Sonrak.

83
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,560
They're professionals.

84
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:32,159
We're just ordinary people.

85
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,840
How could we ever keep up with them?

86
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:35,400
I think there might be cops

87
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,320
working with them.

88
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,000
Captain Tom?

89
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,640
He's the most suspicious.

90
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,680
If the evidence clearly links him,

91
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,960
I'll deal with him for sure.

92
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,240
Sonrak.

93
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,120
I want you to trust me completely.

94
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,440
When they get caught like this,

95
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:57,160
they'll try to frame me and the company

96
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,080
to escape punishment.

97
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,840
But I swear,

98
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:06,480
I've never done anything wrong,
never had an evil thought.

99
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:08,040
You need to stay firm.

100
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,400
Don't be easily swayed.

101
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:12,320
And don't listen to those two, understand?

102
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,360
I'm a cop.

103
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,480
I always stand on the side of justice.

104
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:20,200
And I promise you,

105
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:23,200
Mr. Singha is a good man.

106
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:28,360
I trust my dad. I know
he wouldn't do anything bad.

107
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,400
You brought us here.

108
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,120
Can we trust this person?

109
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,840
You can trust him.

110
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:53,920
Kamnan?

111
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,080
Captain Tom told me everything.

112
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:00,320
You can stay here safely, don't worry.

113
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,520
This way, you can keep working smoothly.

114
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:06,200
Why are you helping us?
What about Singha and the others?

115
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:10,160
Do you think I'm on their side?

116
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,920
Hey, Ice!

117
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,280
Are you working for Kamnan?

118
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:23,440
Yes. Uncle Kamnan sent me
to investigate Mr. Singha and Mr. Kitti,

119
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,640
because he suspected
something was wrong with the finances.

120
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:29,560
Once I found out
they were breaking the law,

121
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:33,360
I quietly reported on them
and collected evidence at the same time.

122
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,840
The evidence Ms. Ice provided
to the authorities

123
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:40,920
is very valuable. It shows
their illegal financial activities.

124
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,520
Now they won't get away.

125
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,680
Kamnan.

126
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:50,040
-What is it?
-There's news

127
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,400
about Ms. Onanong and Mr. Phupha.

128
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,160
Huh? Why is the door open like this?

129
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,520
Let's go check upstairs.

130
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:08,880
Let's go.

131
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,640
Teacher.

132
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:25,800
What happened? Who would do this?

133
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,120
Aunt Wilai.

134
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,440
Aunt Wilai!

135
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:34,520
Aunt Wilai! Are you here?

136
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,480
Wilai!

137
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,240
Wilai!

138
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,120
Wilai!

139
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,600
Oh no.

140
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,480
We don't know where Aunt Wilai is.

141
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:46,640
What should we do?

142
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,960
Trust me.

143
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,000
She must have escaped.

144
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:57,280
Geez, people these days.

145
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:00,320
They're so cruel.

146
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:03,160
Look at this.
Everything's been thrown everywhere.

147
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:19,160
Teacher.

148
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,920
What's this tape?

149
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,000
It's a home video.

150
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,120
Your mom loved filming and keeping these.

151
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,000
Mom?

152
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:39,480
NAMTHIP, ONANONG

153
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:42,080
"Namthip, Onanong."

154
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,480
Do you have a video player?

155
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,920
I want to see her when she was alive.

156
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,440
I miss Mom.

157
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:13,040
<i>Come on, smile sweetly for us.</i>
<i>Yes, beautiful!</i>

158
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,640
<i>Here it is.</i>

159
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,840
<i>"Waiting for Him to Forget".</i>

160
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:19,320
<i>Wow, your mom</i>

161
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,880
<i>is a million-selling singer!</i>

162
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,360
<i>I'm blushing!</i>

163
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,960
<i>Let me hear your little voice.</i>

164
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,320
<i>Whoa!</i>

165
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:30,360
<i>Oh!</i>

166
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:32,480
<i>My niece kicked me! Ouch!</i>

167
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:35,520
<i>My niece kicked me!</i>

168
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,040
<i>Calm down, dear.</i>

169
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,880
<i>Wow!</i>

170
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,040
<i>She's so strong, On!</i>

171
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:44,920
<i>So strong! My niece is really strong!</i>

172
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,120
"SOFT HEART"

173
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,760
Oh, what's this, my friend?

174
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:51,520
Hey, turn this way real quick!

175
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:55,080
It's a new song. I wrote it a while ago.

176
00:13:56,960 --> 00:14:00,400
Wow, let me see!

177
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:02,600
Hmm.

178
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,960
"What is it about this man?

179
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:08,480
Every time I see his face,
my heart pounds."

180
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,480
Wow!

181
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:15,400
So sweet! What's going on?
Let me interview you!

182
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:20,120
<i>This song's called "Soft Heart".</i>

183
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,800
<i>I wrote it</i>

184
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:24,800
<i>for the man I love the most.</i>

185
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,960
<i>It's so sweet,</i>
<i>we're all getting a sugar high!</i>

186
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:35,400
-My stomach hurts!
-Your stomach?

187
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,720
Take me to the hospital.

188
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,440
Okay.

189
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,880
I'll take you there. Let's go!

190
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,840
Your stomach hurts? Careful, On!

191
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:45,760
-Is the baby coming?
-I think so.

192
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:48,480
Slow down, On. Let's go!

193
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,840
<i>Thank you, my dear,</i>

194
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:53,080
<i>for being my baby.</i>

195
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,720
<i>I promise</i>

196
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,520
<i>I'll take good care of you,</i>

197
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:58,680
<i>no matter what happens.</i>

198
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,960
<i>Auntie too!</i>

199
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:03,200
I'll take care of you well.

200
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,080
Hm.

201
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:06,880
-On, by the way,
-Huh?

202
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:09,000
what do you want to name the baby?

203
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:14,880
<i>Since she was born,</i>
<i>she's never caused me any trouble.</i>

204
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:19,680
<i>She may be small, but her hands</i>
<i>are strong like crab claws!</i>

205
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:23,320
<i>Every time you pinch me, it hurts!</i>

206
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:28,560
<i>I'll name you</i>

207
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,120
<i>Puna.</i>

208
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,560
Is this real, Teacher?

209
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:00,920
I'm…

210
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:03,320
I'm Aunt Wilai's child?

211
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:09,920
Puna.

212
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,880
Everything you just saw is true.

213
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,880
It's time you knew

214
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,200
your real mother is Onanong,

215
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,600
not Namthip.

216
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,400
Wilai! Wilai.

217
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,360
Yes?

218
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,960
Today I feel like

219
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:33,080
you love Puna
and care for her especially.

220
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,040
Listen carefully, Mueangphrai.

221
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:39,880
I have to love

222
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,800
and care for Puna even more,

223
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,360
as much as a mother possibly could.

224
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,080
Huh?

225
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,920
A mother?

226
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:53,280
You mean Puna…

227
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,800
Yes.

228
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,200
Puna is my child.

229
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,800
Really, Wilai?

230
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,480
I'm telling you the truth.

231
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,240
What about her father?

232
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,720
Then why did everyone lie to me?

233
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,960
You have to understand.

234
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:16,680
Back then,

235
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:19,640
singers couldn't get married
or have a family.

236
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,560
At that time, Onanong was a rising star,

237
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:25,000
gaining fame and recognition.

238
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:53,080
<i>Deceiving, making me</i>

239
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:57,160
<i>Wait for you</i>

240
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,520
Amazing!

241
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,960
I guarantee

242
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:02,920
your first album

243
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,160
is going to sell like crazy.

244
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,520
Well…

245
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,400
Sorry, Boss. I need to step out.

246
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:22,720
Are you pregnant?

247
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:27,640
Boss.

248
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:33,120
I just found out when I came to Bangkok.

249
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,040
You know

250
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,680
what has to be done about this.

251
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,040
No.

252
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:42,360
I absolutely won't do that.

253
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:45,120
Do you know how much I've invested in you?

254
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,960
If a singer is involved with a guy,

255
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:49,640
no matter how good the song is,
it won't sell.

256
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,800
Please, Boss.

257
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:56,760
Please let me keep this child.

258
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,920
I promise I won't let anyone know.

259
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,840
Boss. Boss!

260
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,080
I'm begging you.

261
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,600
I won't let anyone find out.

262
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,200
I'll make sure there's no suspicion.

263
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:11,760
I won't cause you any trouble.

264
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:14,680
Please, Boss. I promise.

265
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,280
I won't let anyone know, I swear!

266
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:17,880
Please.

267
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,360
-Please, Boss.
-On.

268
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,720
For the sake of your voice,

269
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,320
I'll give you a chance.

270
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:32,160
Thank you, Boss.

271
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,680
Thank you.

272
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:42,480
This is your father, my dear.

273
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,960
Your father's name is Phupha.

274
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:47,640
I love your father very much.

275
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:51,360
"WAITING FOR HIM TO FORGET"

276
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,920
Can your friend take the baby
back to the countryside?

277
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,360
If the truth comes out one day,

278
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,280
your future will be ruined.

279
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:08,000
But she's still so little, Boss.

280
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,640
Please give me a little more time.

281
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:12,160
Onanong.

282
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:15,440
Your career is on the rise now.

283
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:18,200
Money is pouring in.

284
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:20,840
Opportunities like this come only once.

285
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,080
If you miss it, it's gone.

286
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,960
Think carefully.

287
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,840
And another thing,

288
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,560
you know I've invested ten million in you.

289
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,520
You're not just putting yourself at risk.

290
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,680
You could bankrupt me too.

291
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:38,760
Yes.

292
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,760
Namthip, give this money to Phupha.

293
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:09,280
For what?

294
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:13,640
When I ran away to Bangkok,

295
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:18,400
Phupha mortgaged his farmland
to pay for his mother's treatment.

296
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,560
If he doesn't have the money
to redeem it yet,

297
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:24,160
give it to him.

298
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,920
Okay. But will he take it?

299
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Right now, he misunderstands.

300
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:35,480
He thinks you left him because he's poor.
He probably won't accept your money.

301
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,720
Then tell him it's your money.

302
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:42,560
Say you're lending it to him
to save the land.

303
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,320
But the most important thing,

304
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:48,400
you must keep it a secret about Puna.

305
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:52,000
Don't let him know she's our child.

306
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,040
Got it.

307
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,160
No one will suspect a thing.

308
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,240
I promise.

309
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:03,080
Only you and I will know about this.

310
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,160
Thip.

311
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:12,000
I know

312
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,600
you love Phupha too.

313
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:17,680
On.

314
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:22,480
If Phupha ever loves again,

315
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,920
I want him to open his heart to you.

316
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,720
It would be good

317
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:33,080
if you and him could end up together

318
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,720
and have Puna as your child.

319
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:45,440
No. You and Phupha must be together.
One day, you'll be.

320
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:48,520
That's impossible, Thip.

321
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:51,560
I've gone too far,
there's no turning back.

322
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:54,120
Go, Thip.

323
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:57,560
Take Puna to Phupha.

324
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,480
Please make her your child too.

325
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,360
I'm sorry.

326
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:12,040
Goodbye, my dear.

327
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:25,680
I promise

328
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:28,160
I'll take care of Puna as best as I can.

329
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,640
I'll be her mother.

330
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:36,480
I'll love her like any mother would.

331
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:44,360
Don't worry, On.

332
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:01,280
Alright.

333
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:21,800
Take care of my child.

334
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,840
Puna, my dear.

335
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,040
I'm going.

336
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:30,280
I'm going now.

337
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,920
Here you go.

338
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:24,520
Thank you so much, Namthip.
I'll pay it all back when I can.

339
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,600
Oh, it's okay.

340
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,920
I'm not in a hurry.

341
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,920
There, there.

342
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,560
Don't cry, dear. Don't cry.

343
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:37,600
This is your baby, Namthip?

344
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:40,840
Yes.

345
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:44,360
And the father?

346
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,640
We've broken up.

347
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,240
Well…

348
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:52,160
Let's not talk about this again, Phupha.

349
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,440
I'm sorry.

350
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:56,120
It's okay.

351
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,760
She's so cute. What's her name?

352
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,480
Puna.

353
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:03,880
Puna?

354
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:06,440
There, there.

355
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:08,440
Can I hold her?

356
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,000
Of course.

357
00:26:12,120 --> 00:26:13,560
Gently now.

358
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:16,360
-Here, hold her.
-Okay.

359
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:29,440
Look, Namthip. She stops fussing
when she's with me.

360
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,320
Puna

361
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:33,040
likes you.

362
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:34,920
Namthip.

363
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,200
-I really like this little one.
-Yes?

364
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:40,800
Oh.

365
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,680
-Aw.
-Oh.

366
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:44,800
She really likes you.

367
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:47,920
Hey.

368
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:48,880
Little one.

369
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,280
Want to stay with me?

370
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:53,880
Huh?

371
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:04,720
Aw.

372
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:07,440
Aw.

373
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,160
The baby is really easy to take care of.

374
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,320
<i>She doesn't cry at all during the night.</i>

375
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:19,040
Right now, she's playing with Phupha.

376
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:20,880
Really? Well…

377
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:23,480
Does Phupha love Puna?

378
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:25,080
Of course, he does.

379
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,040
He's very attached to her now.

380
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:30,480
I'm glad to hear that.

381
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:33,560
On.

382
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:38,080
I have something important to tell you.

383
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,000
Sure. What is it?

384
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:44,760
Is it okay

385
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:46,960
if I marry Phupha?

386
00:27:55,800 --> 00:28:00,120
On, I'm sorry, I mean…

387
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,720
-<i>I mean…</i>
-Don't worry, Thip.

388
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:05,160
I haven't said anything bad to you.

389
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:10,160
If you and Phupha truly love each other,

390
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:11,920
I'm happy for you.

391
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:15,400
You're my best friend.

392
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:19,320
I believe you'll take good care of him.

393
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:23,840
I hope you two
will love each other very much.

394
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,560
How's our little girl, Namthip?

395
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:33,320
First day at school,
she didn't cry at all.

396
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:35,160
-Really?
-Yeah.

397
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,800
My little girl is so strong.

398
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:38,720
Yes.

399
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,200
Puna's strong, just like you, On.

400
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:44,880
How about you and Phupha?

401
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:48,720
He treats me well, respectful and kind.

402
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:52,440
But in his heart, it's always been you.

403
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:55,800
I'm not jealous though.

404
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:58,960
I love Phupha for who he is.

405
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:00,240
And I love you too.

406
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:03,800
Phupha's here!

407
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:07,680
Oh, what do I do?
I don't want him to see me.

408
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:09,360
Well then.

409
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:11,360
Hide over there. Walk slowly.

410
00:29:13,240 --> 00:29:14,160
Hey.

411
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,480
You haven't gone to get her yet, Namthip?

412
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:17,800
I'm about to.

413
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:20,560
-Then I'll go pick her up myself.
-Okay.

414
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:23,760
Hey, Tharin!

415
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:29,520
I saw you entered the singing contest?

416
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:31,600
The papers were all over it.

417
00:29:31,680 --> 00:29:32,960
That's right.

418
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:35,680
You sneaked into the contest quietly,
didn't tell anyone.

419
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:37,840
I was scared I'd get eliminated
and embarrass myself.

420
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:41,760
But the papers said you won an award.

421
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:45,000
Well, just first runner-up.

422
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,400
I'm happy for you.

423
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:51,080
So you'll be the new artist
at Darathong Music, right?

424
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:55,360
I've dreamed of being a singer
since I was a kid.

425
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:59,200
Kamnan will call me soon
to sign the contract.

426
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:01,560
I'll become an artist at Darathong Music

427
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,920
and have my own songs.

428
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:10,160
If Puna knew, she'd be so happy, Phupha.

429
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,440
Puna loves singing too.

430
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:14,960
If she knew you were becoming a singer,

431
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:17,000
she'd probably scream with joy.

432
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:21,360
Congrats! You're amazing!

433
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:29,600
Back then, our family was in trouble.

434
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:32,680
Everyone had to raise money
to redeem the mortgaged farmland.

435
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:36,080
Both Phupha and Onanong
struggled to get the money.

436
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:38,080
Everyone had to make sacrifices.

437
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:40,640
Puna being Namthip's child,

438
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:43,040
that was the best choice at the time.

439
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:46,640
Do you know how painful it was

440
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:49,480
for a mother not to have a chance
to be with her child?

441
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:56,760
She didn't do it selfishly, Puna.

442
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:00,960
She did it for everyone.

443
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:06,960
I understand now, Teacher.

444
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:11,960
I understand everything.

445
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:17,440
Where's my mom?

446
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,800
I want to pay my respects.

447
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:23,440
Teacher.

448
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:28,480
I understand now.

449
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:31,240
I want to see Mom.

450
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:35,200
Mom…

451
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:42,560
Who is it?

452
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:44,280
This is Boon.

453
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:54,160
Kamnan called.

454
00:31:54,840 --> 00:31:55,920
Yes.

455
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,040
Thank you.

456
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,200
Yes, Kamnan.

457
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,280
How are you, On?

458
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:07,680
Do you need anything?

459
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,680
No.

460
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,400
Thank you so much, Kamnan,

461
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,320
for giving me a safe place
in an emergency.

462
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:16,360
Actually, I had my people

463
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:18,360
watch over your safety from a distance.

464
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,160
So when you needed help,

465
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:23,480
they were able to step in immediately.

466
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:27,760
If it weren't for your help,
I'd be in serious trouble.

467
00:32:27,840 --> 00:32:29,760
Thank you again, Kamnan.

468
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:31,280
Right now,

469
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:33,960
Singha and his group know

470
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:36,240
that you and Phupha are still alive.

471
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,520
Don't go anywhere
unless absolutely necessary.

472
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,080
Thank you very much.

473
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,880
What about Phupha?

474
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,520
He's safe.

475
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:50,120
But someone's keeping watch at his house.

476
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:53,360
I think they want to use him

477
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:55,800
to lure you out.

478
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:58,760
I want to contact Phupha

479
00:32:58,840 --> 00:33:00,320
to let him know.

480
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:03,080
But right now, I can't reach him at all.

481
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:04,680
On.

482
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:07,600
Phupha is smart.

483
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:10,320
He already knows,

484
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:12,160
that's why he turned off his phone

485
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,520
for everyone's safety.

486
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:17,160
<i>For now, use my phone.</i>

487
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:19,760
Don't turn on yours.

488
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:20,800
It could be dangerous.

489
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:24,880
And most importantly,
don't call Phupha, no matter what.

490
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:27,840
Then can I call someone else?

491
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:29,920
<i>Only if it's necessary.</i>

492
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:31,920
It's dangerous.

493
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:35,800
Yes, Kamnan. Thank you.

494
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:51,200
Tharin!

495
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,080
Tharin!

496
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:55,120
Oh, Sroi. Come in.

497
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:00,280
Why are you shutting the doors?

498
00:34:00,360 --> 00:34:02,080
I called you, but couldn't reach you.

499
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,040
I brought some curry for you.

500
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:12,239
Those guys,

501
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:14,600
they've been watching me for a while now.

502
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:18,000
They're probably
the ones who killed Phupha.

503
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:19,679
Oh no.

504
00:34:20,239 --> 00:34:21,840
It's not over yet?

505
00:34:21,920 --> 00:34:23,280
Should I call the police?

506
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,719
We can't. The cops are on their side.

507
00:34:26,679 --> 00:34:29,199
Sroi, don't let them suspect
that you know anything.

508
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:31,320
Sure, I won't tell anyone.

509
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:36,000
Are they going to kill you too, Tharin?

510
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,719
If they wanted me dead,
they'd have done it already.

511
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:41,920
I suspect

512
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:45,320
they have some kind of plan.

513
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,639
What kind of plan?

514
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:48,440
Don't worry about that yet, Sroi.

515
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:51,560
Anyway, can I ask you
to deliver a message?

516
00:34:51,639 --> 00:34:53,360
What message?

517
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:57,320
Tell Puna to be careful.

518
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:59,520
And to stay far away from this.

519
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:04,520
It's dangerous. She shouldn't come back
unless it's necessary.

520
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:10,600
Stop crying, Puna.

521
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:13,480
From now on, you need
to be strong for your parents.

522
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,480
It's such a shame, Teacher.

523
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:20,400
I finally got my mom back.

524
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,760
But my dad isn't here.

525
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:26,600
One more thing.

526
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:28,440
You probably don't know this.

527
00:35:30,600 --> 00:35:31,880
What is it?

528
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:33,840
The person who died
in the car 20 years ago

529
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,120
wasn't your dad.

530
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,800
It was Uncle Tharin.

531
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,160
What do you mean?

532
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:43,480
Your mom told me,

533
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:47,440
when she was fleeing,
the people in the car were Uncle Tharin

534
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:48,680
and Namthip.

535
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:50,320
Not Phupha.

536
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,920
But the criminals didn't know

537
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,560
your dad had a twin.

538
00:35:56,640 --> 00:35:58,680
So they assumed the one who died

539
00:35:58,760 --> 00:35:59,720
was Phupha.

540
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,880
How did it happen that way?

541
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,400
I found out later,

542
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:07,880
on that day,

543
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:10,240
Phupha was driving the car,
got into an accident,

544
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:11,600
and passed out.

545
00:36:16,240 --> 00:36:18,000
Namthip, pick up.

546
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,320
Where are you?

547
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,680
Hey!

548
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:33,520
Phupha!

549
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,600
Pick up, Phupha!

550
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:46,840
Answer me, Phupha!

551
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:53,240
When he woke up,
he realized what had happened.

552
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:56,080
He decided to disguise himself as Tharin,

553
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:58,240
copying the way he walked.

554
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:00,640
That's right.

555
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:03,960
I remember now.

556
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:06,560
I've seen it before.

557
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:13,720
Hey, Puna.

558
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:15,800
Is your leg better now?

559
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:17,400
Well…

560
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,960
Puna, dear.

561
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:26,560
About my leg,

562
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:28,480
don't tell anyone, okay?

563
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:30,480
Why not?

564
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:34,720
Well, if I walk normally,

565
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:36,120
someone might try to kill me.

566
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:39,320
You don't want me to die, right?

567
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:41,680
No, I don't want you to die.

568
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:42,920
Then,

569
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,520
you have to forget about my leg.

570
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:47,440
And don't ever mention it again.

571
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:49,600
Don't let anyone know, understand?

572
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:50,800
I understand.

573
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,480
Promise me, okay?

574
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:02,960
Since that time,

575
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:06,720
Uncle Tharin has been much more careful.

576
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:12,400
But as I grew up, I forgot about it.

577
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:16,560
Hearing you talk just now reminded me.

578
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:19,680
Actually, your mom and I

579
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:22,680
tried to get him to admit it.

580
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:24,240
But your father is stubborn.

581
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,960
He's worried about safety.

582
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,760
It's not

583
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:30,640
just his own,

584
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:33,240
but yours as well, Puna.

585
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,200
It turns out

586
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:39,240
I have both my mom and dad

587
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:42,640
always by my side.

588
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,000
Not for much longer, dear.

589
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:46,240
You'll meet your parents soon.

590
00:38:47,080 --> 00:38:48,240
I truly believe that.

591
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,000
There's no chance anymore.

592
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:17,160
I appreciate your feelings.

593
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,080
But I need to be honest.

594
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:21,800
There's no way

595
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:23,160
this can work between us.

596
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:27,040
-Excuse me.
-Puna.

597
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:29,960
Puna, listen to me! Puna!

598
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:40,400
What's wrong?

599
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:49,600
It's nothing. I'm fine.

600
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:52,720
Are you crying?

601
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:58,880
Who did this to you?

602
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:00,200
Tell me.

603
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:02,400
No one.

604
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:05,240
Tell me, who hurt you?

605
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:07,800
Puna, was it?

606
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:14,440
You love her that much?

607
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:16,960
But she doesn't love me, Dad!

608
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:19,800
There are plenty of other girls, son.

609
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:22,640
But no one else is like her, Dad.

610
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:26,840
Come here.

611
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,360
If you love Puna that much,

612
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:33,160
I'll take care of it.

613
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:37,840
How will you take care of it?

614
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:40,120
You don't need to know.

615
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:42,560
Just trust me.

616
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:45,720
I won't let you down, okay?

617
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:52,360
BAI TONG MUSIC

618
00:40:57,120 --> 00:40:59,240
Huh? Who's calling?

619
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:03,200
Hello?

620
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:04,240
<i>Mueangphrai.</i>

621
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,400
It's me.

622
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:07,000
Wilai!

623
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,880
Whose phone are you calling from?

624
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:10,560
Where are you now?

625
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:13,040
At Kamnan's family resort.

626
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:14,480
I'll come see you.

627
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:16,600
Okay, I actually wanted to see you.

628
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:18,680
I'll send you the location.

629
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:24,000
BREAKING! YOUNG POLICE OFFICERS
LINKED TO DRUG TRAFFICKING CASE

630
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,120
Puna!

631
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:29,200
Is this news true?

632
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,640
It's not true. They were set up.

633
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:35,080
But with news like this,

634
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,720
we probably can't even invite him
to sign with our label,

635
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:38,880
right, Dam?

636
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:41,840
You were planning
to invite Chaiya to be a singer too?

637
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:42,960
Yes!

638
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:44,880
The boss has already given
the green light.

639
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:46,560
But why is he doing this?

640
00:41:50,240 --> 00:41:52,920
Hey! What are you all chatting about?

641
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,880
-Break it up!
-Break it up?

642
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:57,160
Break it up! Break it up!

643
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:03,720
Puna.

644
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:06,920
The media for the interview just called.
They're almost here.

645
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,680
The interview goes until noon.
If it runs long, it could go even longer.

646
00:42:11,760 --> 00:42:12,680
Got it.

647
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:22,240
Teacher, if the interview runs long,

648
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:23,960
I probably won't get to see Mom today.

649
00:42:24,040 --> 00:42:25,240
Then I'll go myself.

650
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:30,320
The other day, Aunt Sroi said
Dad wants me to stay away.

651
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,720
He's worried about danger.

652
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,720
But I won't run away, Teacher.

653
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:37,240
I need to find that tape.

654
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:39,640
It has to be somewhere.

655
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,200
I believe that too.

656
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,840
Be careful.

657
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:45,360
Don't worry.

658
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:47,920
They're not after me. I'll be fine.

659
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:53,520
Puna, the interviewer is here. Get ready.

660
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:55,360
Okay.

661
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,600
I'll go then.

662
00:42:57,680 --> 00:42:58,600
Take care, Teacher.

663
00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:06,000
Let's see. Is everything okay?

664
00:43:14,560 --> 00:43:15,400
What would you like?

665
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:18,960
We will order later.

666
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,120
Okay.

667
00:43:25,320 --> 00:43:27,400
-Mueangphrai.
-What?

668
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:45,120
Chart is over there.

669
00:43:46,440 --> 00:43:48,840
-Huh?
-That guy, Chart!

670
00:43:56,800 --> 00:43:57,880
Tharin.

671
00:43:59,280 --> 00:44:00,800
Chart is right behind you.

672
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:19,320
It really is him.

673
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:22,760
We need to talk about this today.

674
00:44:22,840 --> 00:44:25,520
The other day, someone
was following us to the house.

675
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:30,680
Wilai.

676
00:44:31,600 --> 00:44:33,440
It feels like someone's following us.

677
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:41,160
You're right. Let's hurry and get going.

678
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:46,840
I think

679
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:49,560
they know about us.

680
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:53,160
They're following us to kill us again.

681
00:44:57,560 --> 00:44:59,560
I'll kill them right here.

682
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:02,200
Hey! Are you crazy?

683
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:04,520
Think about Puna before doing anything.

684
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:09,280
Let's do this. We get out of here first.

685
00:45:09,360 --> 00:45:10,840
Then regroup.

686
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:12,440
Should we go?

687
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:13,800
They're watching us.

688
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:24,240
Alright.

689
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:27,640
Let's follow my plan.

690
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:41,040
Let's go.

691
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:03,120
Alright.

692
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:04,680
You two go home,

693
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:06,360
pack the clothes you need,

694
00:46:06,440 --> 00:46:07,880
then meet me at the forest edge.

695
00:46:07,960 --> 00:46:09,480
But Tharin…

696
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:11,320
I'll be fine, trust me.

697
00:46:13,920 --> 00:46:16,080
Teacher, take Wilai back first.

698
00:46:18,640 --> 00:46:20,560
Come on, Wilai.

699
00:46:20,640 --> 00:46:22,240
Let's go, quickly.

700
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:24,200
Be careful, okay?

701
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,600
He's gone, Chart.

702
00:46:43,680 --> 00:46:45,280
Trying to lure me, huh?

703
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:47,880
It's not going to be that easy.

704
00:46:49,880 --> 00:46:51,240
He must be somewhere around here.

705
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:53,640
Tod.

706
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:54,960
You check this area carefully.

707
00:46:55,720 --> 00:46:57,280
-I'll go a different way.
-Got it.

708
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:07,600
Don't let me catch you.

709
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:09,360
Hey!

710
00:47:09,440 --> 00:47:10,560
I've been waiting for you.

711
00:47:10,640 --> 00:47:11,840
You bastard!

712
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:48,520
-Hey.
-Ugh.

713
00:48:33,760 --> 00:48:35,520
<i>Chaiya and Manat.</i>

714
00:48:35,600 --> 00:48:37,960
I have no problem if you take them out.

715
00:48:38,520 --> 00:48:39,800
What are you going to do?

716
00:48:39,880 --> 00:48:41,280
Shut you up for good.

717
00:48:41,360 --> 00:48:42,520
You're dead.

718
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:43,880
NEXT EPISODE

719
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:46,680
I've captured Wilai and Tharin.

720
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:49,560
Whether they live or die,

721
00:48:49,640 --> 00:48:51,160
it depends on you.

722
00:48:51,240 --> 00:48:53,280
I'm going to marry you, Mr. Sonrak.

723
00:48:54,640 --> 00:48:56,080
<i>You said it, Puna.</i>

724
00:48:56,160 --> 00:48:58,960
-You!
-No!

725
00:52:00,040 --> 00:52:01,920
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
